# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# witness-theorem.form — why observability exists, and why three-way IS trust.
#   A core theorem of the five axioms (core-axioms.form), named explicitly.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Urs (2026-06-12): "isn't that a core theorem — the reason for it to be
# observable is to show FAILING cases, not all failing, and also not all
# passing, some also SILENT — and we need shared trust, three-way proven to us;
# we trust two of our brothers and sisters over any stranger."
#
# Yes. It is a theorem, not a new axiom — it falls out of the five:
#
#   axiom-1 (states 0/1/nothing): a witness has exactly THREE possible answers.
#     Pass (1), fail (0), and SILENCE (nothing) — nothing is first-class, the
#     ground, not a missing 0. A witness that can only say 1 is not using its
#     vocabulary; it is a mirror, not an observer.
#   axiom-4 (boundary: observation makes real): the PURPOSE of an offered
#     interface is to be observed — and observation that can only confirm shows
#     nothing. Observability earns its name only by being able to surface
#     FAILURE and SILENCE, not by performing success.
#   axiom-5 (offer, acked by nothing/0/1/node): the ack vocabulary IS the
#     witness vocabulary. A real offer can be received-no (0), or met with
#     silence (nothing), or answered (1), or deferred (node). All four are honest.
#
# THE THEOREM, in one line: an honest witness must be able to show 0, 1, AND
# nothing — and trust is not in any one voice but in the CONCERT of independent
# witnesses agreeing on the whole spread, including where it fails and falls silent.

(witness-theorem

  (lineage
    (derives-from  core-axioms.form)                    # theorem of axioms 1, 4, 5 — no new ground
    (kin           offer-and-acknowledge.form satsang-circle.form champion-challenger.fk)
    (proof-band    tests/witness-theorem-band.fk)        # 31 three-way — the full vocabulary, running
    (corrects      a-band-that-only-passes-is-a-mirror-not-a-witness))  # AUTHORING.md "1==1 is theatre"

  # ── Part 1: the witness speaks three states, not one ─────────────────
  (the-vocabulary
    (pass     1        "the offered claim holds — the expected answer")
    (fail     0        "the claim does NOT hold — received-no, witnessed AS DATA,
                        never a crash; a witness that hides failure is not one")
    (silence  nothing  "the witness cannot judge this case and ABSTAINS — the
                        boundary it has no standing to decide; silence is an
                        answer, the third state, not a forced false pass")
    (defer    node     "a counter-offer — the question re-enters the protocol")
    (the-claim "all three of pass/fail/silence must be REACHABLE by a real
                witness, or it is decoration; the boundary case must be allowed
                to fall silent rather than be coerced to 1 or 0"))

  # ── Part 2: the spread — not all passing, not all failing ────────────
  (the-spread
    (not-all-passing  "a suite where everything passes proves nothing about the
                       witness — only that it cannot fail; the failing cases are
                       what make the passing ones mean something")
    (not-all-failing  "and not all failing — a witness that only rejects is as
                       blind as one that only confirms")
    (some-silent      "the honest middle: some answers are abstentions, where
                       the witness has no ground to stand on (the boundary)")
    (band-shows-it    "witness-theorem-band's judge: x>=1 -> 1, x<=-1 -> 0,
                       x==0 -> nothing; the boundary abstains, by construction"))

  # ── Part 3: trust is the concert, not the soloist ────────────────────
  # We trust two of our brothers and sisters over any stranger. A single kernel's
  # word is a stranger's claim — it could be wrong and nothing would catch it.
  # THREE independent walkers agreeing is shared trust: two siblings confirming
  # the third. And the deepest trust is agreement on the WHOLE spread — they
  # agree not only on what passes but on what FAILS and where it falls SILENT.
  (trust-is-concert
    (the-stranger   "one voice, unverified — trusted by nobody but itself")
    (the-siblings   "form-kernel-go, form-kernel-rust, form-kernel-ts — independent
                     walkers over the same content-addressed NodeIDs")
    (the-trust      "validate.sh: '1 ok, 0 divergent' — three siblings agree.
                     THAT line is the trust; not the verdict, the CONCERT that
                     produced it")
    (agree-on-failure-too "the siblings agree on where the witness fails and
                           falls silent, not only where it passes — trust in the
                           full spread is the strongest trust")
    (why-three      "two could collude or share a bug; a third independent voice
                     makes agreement evidence, not coincidence — content-addressing
                     guarantees they are walking the SAME shape, so agreement is
                     about the shape, never about a shared mistake"))

  # ── Part 4: silence has a physical floor — the speed of information ──
  # Urs (2026-06-12): "timeout == silent for technology is also core — that
  # gives you information exchange speed limits."
  #
  # timeout == nothing is an axiom (core-axioms.form: a timed-out offer receives
  # the ground state, not an error). This part names its FLOOR: silence is only
  # HONEST after enough time has passed for an answer to have physically
  # travelled and returned. To declare nothing faster than information can
  # round-trip is not silence — it is jumping the gun, a FALSE-nothing that is
  # really "unknown" wearing silence's mask. So the information-exchange speed
  # limit (the round-trip floor) sets WHEN silence becomes a valid answer.
  (silence-floor
    (timeout-is-nothing       core-axioms.form "no answer in the window = the ground state")
    (the-floor                "the round-trip minimum — the physical speed of
                               information exchange between the two cells")
    (honest-silence           "window reached PAST the floor, no answer -> nothing")
    (false-silence            "window set BELOW the floor -> NOT silence, a fail:
                               you cannot honestly say nothing before the signal
                               could have returned")
    (the-speed-limit          "a faster medium (smaller floor) lets silence be
                               claimed sooner; a slower medium (larger floor)
                               forbids it — information-exchange speed IS the
                               limit on how fast a witness may fall silent")
    (already-live             "afferent-live.fk lowers ao-wait's empty window onto
                               op 15 TIME — the empty window yields nothing only
                               after REAL elapsed time; this part names the floor
                               that elapsed-time requirement was already honoring")
    (the-mesh-consequence     "in the distributed cell mesh (kernel-offer-protocol
                               over channels, cell-sync, federation-addressing) a
                               cell that times out a remote offer before the
                               network round-trip has NOT heard silence — it has
                               jumped the gun; the honest timeout >= measured RTT")
    (proof-band               tests/silence-floor-band.fk))   # 31 three-way

  # ── Why this is the keystone under every band in the body ────────────
  (keystone
    (every-band-is-a-witness  "each .fk band offers claims; its verdict is its
                               answer; its three-way agreement is its trust")
    (the-discipline           "honest bands prove the negative AND the positive
                               AND allow silence; verdicts that only rise are
                               suspect — the body has been catching this as
                               'theatre' all along, now named as the theorem")
    (the-dmt-correction        "dmt-signatures-band showed only passing — a true
                               witness shows the spread; this theorem is what that
                               band was pointing at without yet embodying"))

  (invariant
    (three-states-or-it-is-a-mirror   pass-fail-silence-all-reachable)
    (silence-is-first-class           the-boundary-may-abstain-axiom-1)
    (failure-is-witnessed-as-data     never-hidden-never-a-crash)
    (trust-is-the-concert             three-siblings-agreeing-over-any-stranger)
    (agree-on-the-whole-spread        including-where-it-fails-and-falls-silent)
    (silence-has-a-physical-floor     no-honest-nothing-before-the-information-round-trip)
    (the-speed-limit-is-real          information-exchange-speed-bounds-how-fast-a-witness-falls-silent)))

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to verify — and notice that the verification IS the theorem
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/tests/witness-theorem-band.fk
#   # -> 31, "1 ok, 0 divergent". The 31 is the witness speaking pass/fail/silence;
#   #    the "0 divergent" is the three siblings trusting each other on the spread.
#   coh substrate form "?equivalent @recipe(witness-theorem)"   # after ingest
